-- int_deduped_billing_events.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate model to deduplicate billing events per subscription and month.
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source
WHERE
    row_num = 1
```

-- int_subscription_details.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate model to enrich subscriptions with user, company, and plan dimensions.
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON s.user_id = u.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON u.company_id = c.company_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    tier,
    industry
FROM source
```

-- fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
-- Fact model aggregating monthly subscription metrics by tier and industry.
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        b.event_month AS month,
        sd.tier,
        sd.industry,
        COUNT(b.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
        SUM(b.amount) AS total_mrr,
        COUNT(DISTINCT sd.user_id) AS unique_users
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscription_details') }} sd
        ON b.subscription_id = sd.subscription_id
    GROUP BY
        b.event_month,
        sd.tier,
        sd.industry
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    active_subscriptions,
    total_mrr,
    unique_users
FROM source
